# Module DB File Style Guide

This guide captures conventions observed in module database files (e.g., `context.db.ts`).

## Conventions

- Import enum-like constants from shared constants: `@appname/shared/modules/[feature]/[feature].constants`.
- Define tables with Drizzle's `sqliteTable` as `table` alias.
- Use `uuidv4` as the default for string IDs via `.$default(uuidv4)`.
- Represent booleans with `integer(..., { mode: "boolean" })` and `.default(false)`.
- Represent timestamps with `integer(..., { mode: "timestamp" })` and `.$default(() => new Date())`.
  - `createdAt`: `.$default(() => new Date())`
  - `updatedAt`: `.notNull().$default(() => new Date())`
  - Support soft-deletes/archive via optional `deletedAt`/`archivedAt`.
- JSON columns: `text("col", { mode: "json" }).default([]).$type<string[]>()`.
- Use `references(() => otherTable.id, { onDelete: "cascade" })` for FKs.
- Composite join tables define primary keys with `primaryKey({ columns: [t.aId, t.bId] })`.
- Table names are plural; column names are snake_case at DB level, camelCase in code.

## Example

```typescript
import { SOME_TYPES } from "@app/shared/modules/feature/feature.constants";
import { users } from "@m5kdev/backend/modules/auth/auth.db";
import { integer, primaryKey, sqliteTable as table, text } from "drizzle-orm/sqlite-core";
import { v4 as uuidv4 } from "uuid";

export const items = table("items", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey().$default(uuidv4),
  type: text("type", { enum: SOME_TYPES }).notNull(),
  title: text("title").notNull(),
  flags: text("flags", { mode: "json" }).default([]).$type<string[]>(),
  deletedAt: integer("deleted_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  archivedAt: integer("archived_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).notNull().$default(() => new Date()),
  updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" })
});

export const itemsUsers = table(
  "items_users",
  {
    userId: text("user_id").notNull().references(() => users.id, { onDelete: "cascade" }),
    itemId: text("item_id").notNull().references(() => items.id, { onDelete: "cascade" }),
    enabled: integer("enabled", { mode: "boolean" }).notNull().default(true),
    createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).notNull().$default(() => new Date()),
    updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" })
  },
  (t) => [primaryKey({ columns: [t.userId, t.itemId] })]
);
```

